g.text: The sixth straight day of protests is the largest one yet. Evening sees a turn towards violence; burning and looting begin.
Students across Baltimore stage mass peaceful protests, followed by demonstrations in cities throughout the US, including DC, Manhattan, Minneapolis, and Boston.
The six arresting police officers are charged in Freddie Gray's death.
Gray dies in the hospital after entering a coma during his arrest six days prior. Protests begin in earnest outside the Western District police station.
